you know..after watching america's next top model and looking at these old catalog images..one cant really help but feel sorry for today's model..now they have more than just the 4 poses...hahaha

since other rocks have been turned over..may as well go this way as well...

my ex-bf ...bane of existance...called yesterday to let me know he was leaving town (finally)..all conversations erupted to a screaming match back and forth...luckily while i was alone in my car...not so for the drivers i nearly hit on the way to whole foods..eh..we all made it ok...the former bf..needs to stop this crap..i have a bf...i wouldnt trade him for anything...except maybe as husband..haha...too soon and scary to think about that...

i am bored though...w/this new job...i quit last year the other one...not sure i meant to but alot of things have started just happening on the spur of the moment..i should prob watch myself...told the old firm i wante a month off..and ended up being person #3 to quit in a week...i just needed more free time...and less joe crap...dealing w/ that place and other sitcs. had me on antidepressants...not fun...cause was still low...started this job in Nov..its March now..and still am not where i want to be..am I ever?...i need to make a few calls..i dont need to feel committed w/ these current crazies...

but then i have a purchase agreement out on a house..its pretty cool...2 stories..2004 sf..w/ a separate rentable garage apt in the back thats not part of the sf..they want to much for it like any other greedy morons here in BR..there is a special hell for you...

no word from the murderer next door...i wonder if he is ever going to be convicted..and hopefully i will never have to testify...i wonder sometimes if i can just disappear..but then everyone wants your social..anyone know of any job openings abroad that arent in some sort of field that would get me killed?..i can get that here...

its so muggy hot here..way too early for that nonsense..picked up to start studying for lateral forces/general structures again...my lack of passing is driving thaddeus nuts...definately not a poster child here...and i need to sign up for dorf in houston in april..i need to get this crap done..on the plus side..its the only way i am getting any sleep lately...so it has its uses...for as we all know.."these tests are generally stupid..and I hate them"!!!....i am going to start wearing my "architecture sucks" t-shirt while testing...really ought to piss the NCARB nazis off if they actually review those tapes...do i care...not really...i am certain they think they are going to squeeze every last penny out of me ...so i am certain that they can put up w/ me and my antics...its fair...

well good news...there is an offer...and a counter offer...and a counter offer on the counter offer..am waiting to see if thats accepted...worst time for everthing to hit..but hey... i was bitching about it...

i have scheduled all of my tests-one a week from last month til the end of june..i have site design thurs..just took MEP for the millionth time friday...and have taken building design already...dont ask me how i feel..i try not to anymore...i am just trying to study and get it done..one less freakin hassle..my goal is hawaii in november w/ katrina...in the meantime...test thurs..test next thurs...off to houston for a 5 day structure seminar-covers both general and lateral forces...then the last three tests..boom boom boom..in addition i have my aunt and 2 little cousins coming in this week for about a week...bit of an upset in my schedul...then my grandpa and his wife about the last week of june..so much for that queensrque concert i wanted to go to in NO..but a test early the next morning in BR effectively shoots that down alone itself..and to top it off...big surprise..if this house thing goes through..i have the closing at the end of the month and to be out by july 3rd...and i need to find a new place to live in july...what can i say..when it rains..it pours...bring on the umbrella...its going to be a wild ride...so long as i keep my focus..

now back to the books

buy my house

rent my house

it matters not at this rate...just make it move...so i can move...ready to be full on living in this city..loving it out here...crazy ass drivers though...i dont dare drink in this mess..

i miss my dog..

BUY MY HOUSE

RENT MY HOUSE!!!!

i gotta get out more..but a laptop is addictive...complete power tool at that...

BUY MY HOUSE!!!!

seriously...its an albatross at this point...ah well...this time next week if theres no activity it will go up for rent and i will make a little money....but i dont want the hassle...there are worse things though...in any case...life in NO is going well..i need to force myself to get out more...on the plus side there are pho places out here..now i just gotta get cash on my next trip into BR...NO is definately more of a cash city..forget the plastic unless you are hitting the upscale pricey places...ah well...

lovin this free wireless i can pluck out of the air..how cool is that...

am suppose to work on a habitat house this saturday..have never done that before..should be interesting...have work to continue to do...project due (w/any luck) next friday..then onto a church job and back into inches..tired of the metric system..although it sounds like the aruba ritz carlton may kick up any day now which means we are back to metric..ugh ugh ugh..what genius though that system was great anyway?...bet he was french...

ok....goals for the moment...sell the house...buy a new house local to here so's i can go out and drink in the quarter and walk home..what a goal!..hahaha...take a long weekend to chicago and new york...get some SLEEP!!!!

ok..my first week in NO was exhausting to say the least..i am getting little to no sleep...traffic is crazy..but thats its own story...at least i am only driving in from metarie which is 20-30 minutes vs BR which can be anywhere from 1hr-1.75hrs..depending..drove home and got my dog from my moms friday afternoon..had to endure mike who has become her handyman...i think in an effort to stay close to me...what a control freak...whatever...went to a crawfish boil held by one of our contractors...my boss finally noticed i was in town even though i had been in the office...said something about the ritz-carlton kicking up on the 20th...i think thats the aruba on...i was only half listening and it was noisy...my project is due out on the 22nd and i need a vacation..am seriously burning the candle at both ends..but i dont have it in me to go for very much longer like this...i said i need a vacation..he said no vacations..but we would be extremely well comp'd...well..unless that includes a trip the carribean...i need sleep right now...money doesnt buy sleep at this point..hopefully this week will be better...my project is getting a little straighter...its been a small mess..mostly due to the fact that its a european consultant driven mess...no answers..and they keep changing stuff...so i have tried to do what i can w/ what i have...but it looks like its gotten fairly untangled and i can move on to finishing it..as soon as i have the time...starting tomorrow...today...its back to NO early as i have theater tickets to "movin out"..been looking forward to this one for quite some time...hopefully it lives up to something in my head...

i swear i could have a nervous breakdown if i only had the time..my house has been on the market for a little over a week now..i guess its asking too much to ask it to be SOLD already!!!...i want to pack!!!..i want to move!!!..i have a house in my sights..in the algiers point area..a great little area in new orleans..pricey little area..but safe and worth it...across the river from my job..can take the ferry in or drive over the bridge...new house...new construction..i dont want to do any work..and it will have great re-sale value...i am completely burned out on renovating older houses...i dont want to do that...dont want to touch it w/ a 10' pole..the only problem w/ NO houses are the shotgun style..who the hell wants to walk through all the rooms to get to another room..hello..corridor..that bit drives me nuts..but i found one thats not new but in my price range in the shotgun style..those are just harder to share..and am looking to share at this point...katrina wants to come down..and trying to convince jenn to move in as well..the new construction would be perfect as its 3bdrms 3full baths...all seperated from ea. other..and one of the bed/bath is a mother-in law suite located separately from the house..sweet layout..that house just sang to me...but i gotta sell this one...but at least since i have found what i want i can stop driving into NO every weekend...that was pretty wearing..wont have to go back til april 4th i think..then i am back and forth..there during the week..staying at jenns in metarie..back here on the weekends til the house is settled..craziness...i feel crazy for thinking about it...was going to go to houston this weekend..but i just dont have it in me right now..i gotta finish painting trim...hoping my laptop for the office will be in tomorrow so i can start setting it up this weekend..esp since i will be a combo of working on the house and working in the office...and would rather just stay in one location at this rate...esp since i am holed up redlining here tonight..they are pushing me to get licensed..looking at the next associate..but cant be til i am licensed...too much stuff...my head is gonna explode eventually...i need a vacation from reality..where can i check out?

am transfering to new orleans at the end of the month

am selling my house

beyond that i am a complete mess...

well..am going to take the plunge..hinging on the financial package not yet available at this time...on my way this morning to start scoping out places to live...as they look to have us settled there for april...looking forward to this..but adding a laptop to my list of demands so that i dont have to be stuck in the office working late..and can use it to commute..their idea first really..and i am running w/ it...way excited here...may even get katrina to move out here w/ me..will definately be nearer to jenn..and away from mike..all pluses..only negative is finding new spinning classes etc..eh..if its the only downside..so be it..and gotta get the house going in one way or the other..rent or sell...it matters not...would rather rent..but it cant be a financial burden is all...

ps...have not forgotten your beads..i have been trying to find some bubble wrap as these things have a tendandcy to break if thrown too hard..i should know..i have a couple of broken ones...but i promise i will be sending those as soon as i can..am horrible about mailing stuff..but i will get it done!

ok..gotta go back to work tomorrow..which is going to suck on so many levels..one of them being the fact that i have been off for nearly 2 weeks now...bummer...so much has happened and not..telling things..my brother got a dwi the saturday after thanksgiving..if you can ever avoid this experience..do so..my mom called me at 330am to tell me what had happened..that and she needed me to help her move his car as it was parked sorta illegally..but at least it wasnt towed..which would have been more money...couldnt figure out if his car had the kind w/ the remote that needed to be shut off so we had to drive out to his apt first to find his spare set of keys..not realizing we had the spare set and we only picked up the valet key..no big i guess..his roommate..the guy we werent to pleased about him hanging out w/ in the first place was still waiting for him to come home...they work at the same resturant..and i guess were following each other home..so to speak..and craig hadnt realized that my brother had been pulled over for speeding...anyway..didnt get back home w/ my brothers car til 5am..fell asleep til mike called and woke me up and i told him what was going on...we hadnt heard from my brother about bail..but fortunely mike knew what to do about all of that and who to contact..aparently around here to get bail for a dwi is hard to secure..its such a low cost item no one bothers w/ it..so you really have to call in a favor...so he did that for us...we got my brother out and as far as i know he hasnt had a drink since..which prob isnt the way to go about things either...but at least hes keeping his nose clean for the moment..and then theres the mike situation...bob told us that the world trade center job in new orleans was looking like it was going to be picking up again..which means i may have that opp to be going there and working on that job...i told mike about that and he about blew a gasket...which isnt really fair of him to expect me to be around indefinately if he isnt planning on ever getting married again...because he knows that i want to get married and have a family at some point in time...so how fair is it of him to play this "dog in the manger" shit w/ me?...i dont know for sure that they will put me on the wtc..they asked me months ago if i was interested in going to new orleans but never worked out any details and i sure as hell wouldnt go w/out working out details...but he just flipped..and all this after saying things like never getting married again...ARGH...men....dont ever give me this bullshit about women not knowing what they want...cause men are just as undecided...
but despite all of this we had been back and forth w/ the relationship..keep it going..end it...stay just friends...theres alot going on behind the scenes that i am not going to reveal..some of its just too weird..hehehe...but its come to a head..and finally wed. morning i said fine...lets just be friends..cause there is an aspect that i just cant take in the relationship..and if its a deal-breaker..so be it..but i dont want it there and thats the end of it...well it crushed him...i didnt feel good about it either...and he even admitted i have been the best girlfriend he has ever had...so what the fuck is the problem here?...but its an issue that has to be worked out..and while he is working on it we agreed to not be dating anyone else this next month...still dating each other i guess you could say...but this is getting too complicated...i dont agree w/ how he raises his son...and he wont listen to me on any of that because i dont have a child myself so i must not know a damn thing..which everyone around thinks is bullshit...thats a problem...but regardless i am now banned from his house on the weekends because HE told his child something that wasnt true and disappointed the child and thus its MY fault...but didnt tell me that til a week later...whatever..that just immature on his part...and it frees up my weekends now.....would rather keep it this way since he acts like this...re: his child...overprotective, spoils, the kid will be a terror as he gets older...mark my words...but its not my problem..mike has such a huge guilt complex that he needs to get over and just be a good parent...but he wont..he lets the guilt overrule everything...and thats going to do him in...oh well..not my problem...i wont be around for it..

so its still not over w/ mike..we have been through 2 holidays and 2 full on spaghettis...and he is still around..and dont think i havent tried to drive him away..must be a keeper..he tore down an old shed in my backyard yesterday while i went power shopping w/ my mom w/ everyone else in town...he has plans to help me get my house in shape..he even dug out a piece of metal in my yard thats been pissing me off for 4 years now...what a guy...i would swoon but lets face it..i am just not that kinda girl..but he is impressing the heck out of me..i guess he does care like he says he does..how weird is that from a guy...ok..enough of this nonsense..i have a test on thursday..and somehow i suspect "mike" wont be on it...hahaha

you know..i deleted this thing w/ the purpose of everything going away..but even after 3 months it didnt...so whats that suppose to mean?...that its not suppose to?..that its never going to?...that may be it...i tried the other way and that didnt work..so i came back to my familar standby...i kinda missed this outlet anyway i think...feels more comfortable anyway...

so what did i do on my summer vacation...

i bought a new car...little over two months ago...2004 honda crv power everything/standard 4-wheel drive w/a sunroof and cruise control...andies father gave me a great deal on it and didnt even charge me to have a guy bring it in from shreveport...cause thats where mine was...am i super picky..you bet...but i get what i want..and why not..cause im paying for it..

i have no more credit card debt..or credit cards for that matter...which now my mother tells me i need to have one for back up...forget that...i just keep a healthy balance in savings and pray that if its not enough that someone can float me til payday...i refuse to be a slave to the credit scam anymore...live free!!!

i refinanced my house from 30 years at 7% to 15yrs at 4.875...am paying approx. 100 more a month..but it saves 1000s in interest over the years...and i am planning to pad on an extra payment a year to knock out the payments even quicker...woohoo...

i have started getting my head on straight about taking my tests again...i have my next one scheduled for next month..my goal is to knock them all out by july...pass or fail..and then repeat as necessary...which hopefully wont be necessary..but i am going for it..that "stupid piece of paper"...the ARE is my bitch...i dropped internet from high speed to just above dsl..i practically never use it at home anymore anyway...and now am saving 20/ a month there..and got rid of expanded basic cable...so no distractions w/ the tv...and if i cant handle netflicks..will drop that too...saves money and forces me to focus...no books, no tv-except law and order..thats only 3 hours a week...and the occasional movie breaks on the weekend...after THOROUGH studying...am i harsh or what...i am determined to finish this time...even though it means i will be overworked..but when i leave here..i write my own ticket...fingers crossed...its all about denial...

however to throw a wrench in my well-laid plans..i started dating someone...oh...six weeks ago..as he likes to remind me constantly of how long we have been together..why..i am not really sure...he keeps bringing up forever..i keep saying for now...the idea of forever scares me..the idea of marriage scares me...i can commit...but can he is the question...i guess it boils down to trust...and its too early to worry about this anyway...at least i think so...but he doesnt..he likes to discuss issues...he is divorced...37...has a 4 year old son...thinks i am not quite grounded in reality...like what would happen if i got pregnant during our relationship..and i dont feel thats anything to worry about right now..i mean if it happens...it happens...then worry..but why worry about whats not there in the first place?..i have too many other things to let this be a forethought at this point in time in my life...if all methods of birthcontrol fail..well someone is trying to tell you something and since i want to have a kid at some point in time in my life..it wouldnt be the worst thing to happen to me...getting married on the other hand...is an iffy subject...and i am sooo not ready to deal w/ thoughts on that...weird how that works i guess...augh..too much stuff...

now that i have updated i can go hide again for another 3 months...see ya after the holidays....just kidding..

its is soooooooooooooooooo finally cherry season....i absolutely love cherries...blast that the white cherries are 5$ a lb...and the regular 3$...but oh so worth it...buying them constantly and eating them as often as possible...this is my favorite time of "fruit" year...

would you believe i still think i need a vacation?

somethings gotta give....can i live on 20$/hr in the virgin islands?..where can i get a cost comparison for that?

the date went well...we plan on spending more time together...but taking it slow...which works for me...dont want anymore pressure from anyone at this rate..

found some spinning shoes at an extreme clearance price...little loose at my heel though...got them anyway...mom and i have about the same size...they fit her well...but she is uncertain if she even wants spinning shoes...me..i gotta have em...so will see how they work for me on monday..if too loose i will keep looking for another pair...unless mom decides on tues she isnt ready for shoes...then will find a way to make them work...i cant wait to try them out though..how odd am i...

blind date tomorrow evening w/a guy who has my attention...

he plays soccer...

cross your fingers
ok...my butt is going back to spinning today..and back to the weight machines..i have taken off like a week and a half...gotta get my body moving again...i feel like a slug...not a good feeling

arms, fingers, knees, and toes.....knees and toes...how bizarre is that song

sore abs...been going crunch crazy...starting last night...and boy can i feel them now...avoiding the office tonight...not feeling motivated...pizza and beers on friday...woohoo...its something to look forward to...amanda called this morning..that was whole-y unexpected..she is supposed to call again after nine when my minutes are free...i wonder whats up w/ her...been wondering that all day now..cause she doesnt just call unless theres news..so i am dead curious now...

arms, fingers, knees, and toes.....knees and toes..

ah well...i think i need another sugar-free popscicle...debating on making dumplings..but it feels like too much work...i am so ready for some spagetti..may have to get the stuff to make some this weekend if i cant hold out til next friday...for the big family full on spaghetti in n.c........yumm-o...being good in any case..i resisted sushi tonight w/ heather and her friends.....mainly due to having chicken fried steak w/ mashed tatoes and gravy for lunch...naturally it rained..but today has been a fairly muggy/humid free day..despite all..too weird...ah well...

is it seven more days or six...dont know.....all i know is that this time next wed will be at the airport ready to hop a 730 flight to north carolina...i am ready to go already...but have predicted will feel every single freakin day between now and then due to the project on at work...six more days....

i absolutely love fireworks...went down to the river to see the show after a dinner at my brothers house..this year the thirsty tiger wasnt open...so we didnt have the benefit of watching while listening on the radio...the show was spectacular as always...i dont know why people dont bother w/ it anymore..claudia didnt want to go..my brother didnt want to go..i dont know whats up w/ them...i always found the lights and colors and thundering booms exciting..how could you not...firework displays have got to be the greatest free show ever...always amazing...and its amazing how they make the fireworks..and design them to "burst" a certain way...add that on my list of things i wouldnt mind doing should "architect" not pan out....life is good...was watching a local show w/ a brit for a host...reminds me of that phrase...is he british or is he gay...either way...fascinating to listen to..but he ended his show w/ reflections...like he was thankful that his clothes were snug..for that meant he was well fed...thankful he had bills for it meant there was a roof over his head..thankful when his alarm went off in the morning for it meant he was alive for another day..sorta reverse st francis of assissi..if that makes any sense...but it reminded me to put things in perspective and re-look at my life again..and how truely lucky and blessed i am..despite everything..and i need to remember that...esp when i get all emotional and moody...somebody just slap some sense back into me...

ah the weekend...best one i have had in awhile..the project has been submitted and i have moved on to another project..glory be...went out to the chimes for dinner friday night and then the varsity for the guns n roses tribute band...my brother had me put on the list...he is always comp'd for varsity shows...but rarely goes...so he passed on the savings..woohoo..free show is always nice...stood down at the stage...we had a great time...sure it wasnt the real thing..but hey..at least we werent kept waiting for hours for one song...had seen gnr in 92...it was a long wait then..and to top it all off i had ended my night in a terrible car accident...was lucky enough to live through it..ah well..we pay our debts sometimes...saturday did a whole lot of nothing..re-arranged furniture...did a bit of cleaning...talked w/ claudia...we have ideas for childrens books...an opp to illustrate...its something to do...and i have not felt the creative bug bite in such a long time...i feel almost automated sometimes..sunday was in new orleans for 42nd street..not bad..never seen it before..but the theatre management really hacked me off...lying bastards...just wait til next season...saw the harry potter movie the night it came out...nothing against the movie other than i am always disappointed by the movies after reading the books...i was having to explain them to claudia..and finally i just told her to borrow mine..one at a time..and then we could discuss it...but as a complete outsider to the books the movies did leave gapping holes and unanswered questions...although i did just find out that voldemort will be played by john malkovich..how perfect is that...the weather is oppressively hot...as noted yesterday while in new orleans..and to think..its only june...its gonna be a hot one...mid-july vacation..woohoo.....that i am sooo looking forward to...get out of this state..and away from the humidity...i need to quit saying "i need a vacation"...i need to figure out what the hell happened w/ my mortgage co...did i miss a memo?..got a letter today..a bill from another mortage co...claiming i need to pay them ...well what happened to the check i mailed to my current mortgage co?...i never got anything informing me that i was being switched...fucking morons...back to the house crap that i hate....just when things are going swimmingly..they screw you up...yeah...couldnt see that coming...ah well..wendy is in italy now...my brother and his roommate are in houston..i want to be anywhere but here sometimes....just dont want the hassle of hauling everything off as well...had bought ceiling fans at home depot memorial day weekend..but now see ones at lowes that i would prefer that cost less...guess i gotta get back to the store..i wish this rain would just rain and go...course then its back to the oppressive sun and humidity...which i am not sure is any worse than the rain and oppressive humidity..who can tell anymore...not i.....

apparently i am not too young to have high blood pressure out of control...chalk it up to stress...on the positive side i have dropped 14lbs since mid-april...we think we have finally reigned in the blood pressure problem although the doc tells me now i need to stop taking so much ibprofuen and advil...if i am continuing to have bad headaches he will prescribe something else for me...should the anaprox stop working...i hate taking the anaprox...i hate the stress...i literally had a mini-breakdown on friday...while on the phone to wendy over working overtime...i had hit my limit...havent been sleeping..i do make sure i hit the gym religiously though...started weight training again..and got so involved that i overdid it tues nite so that i was in major pain on wed...i can take my office in about 2 hour intervals..and then i just want to leave for a bit...unfortunately lunch isnt for another 2 hours when it hits...and then in the afternoon i still have another 2 hours when it hits again...thankfully its friday tomorrow...pizza and beers..and the new harry potter movie...the boys who got the office party to plan this month have chosen paintball wars...oh yeah...i am sooooo there.....w/my hit list..and as wendy pointed out..this could get ugly fast....i dont care anymore....i have booked the tickets for north carolina next month...gonna do some looking around while out there...i came to the realization after rooting around my attic over the weekend that i could sell this house...tired of attachments...did some planting of major plants in my yard over the weekend...am doing a swell job of lining plants up about a foot from the fence spaced about 3-4 feet apart...completely accidently really...but looking at it all after my brother mowed down the grass...it looks good...i have also decided i am going to get a kiddie pool....for those relaxing moments in the backyard...i can only imagine what the neighbors are going to think..and quite frankly i couldnt care less...they are already puzzled about the "landmines" - remnants of the southdowns parade...i need to find and scan pics of that float by the way and post them...i am scattered...i need to sleep...its just not been happening...and now i am thinking i should write a book..i have 2 ideas fleshed out in an outline...gotta do some research though...i have a sore throat..have i mentioned that already...scattered...very scattered
